        <abstract>
            <p>Encloses extract [missing] on a caterpillar.</p> 
<p>Mentions William Buckler’s magnificent drawings of caterpillars [<hi rend="italic">The larvae of the British butterflies and moths</hi>, Ray Soc. (1886–91)], but doubts Buckler will lend them for any Darwinian purpose. John Hellins has a portion of drawings and is more liberal.</p> 
